Will it not?

11
00:03:14,124 --> 00:03:15,303
我得走了
I must be off.

12
00:03:16,106 --> 00:03:19,607
这些人都要通知到
You can acknowledge all of these.

13
00:03:20,182 --> 00:03:21,628
这家伙不错
There's a good chap.

14
00:03:21,665 --> 00:03:23,023
谢谢
Thanks.

15
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:23,923
父亲
Father?

16
00:03:23,961 --> 00:03:25,224
亲爱的 什么事
My dear?

17
00:03:25,261 --> 00:03:27,817
昨晚你听到Roy的叫声了么
Did you hear how Roy barked last night?

18
00:03:27,854 --> 00:03:29,835
太可怕了
It was dreadful.

19
00:03:29,913 --> 00:03:31,414
不 我没有听见
No, no I didn't.

20
00:03:32,182 --> 00:03:33,245
你听见了么 Bennett
Did you hear him Bennett?

21
00:03:33,282 --> 00:03:34,954
我也没有 先生
I can't say I did, sir.

22
00:03:34,991 --> 00:03:36,706
它不停地叫
He kept on and on.

23
00:03:36,742 --> 00:03:39,306
还在咆哮
He howled too.

24
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:41,800
肯定是有人进了花园
I'm sure someone got into the garden.

25
00:03:41,837 --> 00:03:43,509
有人闯入?
An intruder?

26
00:03:43,546 --> 00:03:46,145
是的 因为
Well yes, because.

27
00:03:46,182 --> 00:03:48,197
哦 父亲
Oh father

28
00:03:48,554 --> 00:03:50,901
有人从窗户外
someone looked in at me,

29
00:03:51,527 --> 00:03:52,428
看着我
at my window.

30
00:03:52,466 --> 00:03:54,947
不可能
Impossible.

31
00:03:55,637 --> 00:03:57,948
你是在做梦吧
You must have been dreaming.

32
00:03:57,986 --> 00:04:01,726
Edith 没人能爬到你的窗口
Oh, Edith nobody could reach your window.

33
00:04:01,762 --> 00:04:04,093
窗户离地面太远了
It's far too far off the ground.

34
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:07,067
我肯定不是在做梦
I'm sure I wasn't dreaming.

35
00:04:07,949 --> 00:04:09,642
Bennett 你来负责
Bennett, you take charge

36
00:04:09,679 --> 00:04:11,735
不然我就赶不上参加教工会议了
or I shall be late for the faculty meeting.

37
00:04:11,772 --> 00:04:14,217
我让你的未婚夫来照顾你 亲爱的
I leave you in your fiance's care my dear.

38
00:04:14,253 --> 00:04:16,034
如果他做你的丈夫
If he proves as good a husband to you as

39
00:04:16,071 --> 00:04:17,348
也能像做我的助理那么出色
he has amanuenses to me,

40
00:04:17,385 --> 00:04:19,324
你就是个幸运的女人
you'll be a fortunate woman.

41
00:04:20,469 --> 00:04:23,380
缓和一下她的恐惧情绪 Bennett 我知道你能做到
Allay her fears Bennett. I know you can.

42
00:04:23,888 --> 00:04:25,264
你相信我么
Can you believe me?

43
00:04:25,902 --> 00:04:27,100
没法轻易相信啊
Not easily, no.

44
00:04:27,136 --> 00:04:28,599
就像你父亲说的
I mean as your father said.

45
00:04:28,637 --> 00:04:29,943
那你就来看看
Come and look.

46
00:04:29,979 --> 00:04:33,431
我实在是太忙了 这些关于松鼠猴的笔记要打印
I'm awfully busy with these notes on Saimiri Sciureus to type,

47
00:04:33,468 --> 00:04:34,599
然后是你父亲关于论证...
and then the proof of your father's...

48
00:04:34,636 --> 00:04:38,989
Jack 我不是在做梦
Jack, I know I wasn't dreaming

49
00:04:39,026 --> 00:04:42,262
你知道Roy不会无缘无故乱叫
and you know Roy doesn't bark at nothing.

50
00:04:42,298 --> 00:04:43,988
我希望你亲自去看看
I want you to see for yourself.

51
00:04:44,025 --> 00:04:46,547
你必须来看看 求你了
You must. Please.

52
00:04:47,984 --> 00:04:49,937
在狗叫声吵醒我之后
And then after the barking woke me

53
00:04:49,975 --> 00:04:53,022
我听到了别的声音 从那下面传来的
I heard another sound from just below here.

54
00:04:53,059 --> 00:04:54,624
从那下面?
From below?

55
00:04:54,660 --> 00:04:56,797
这 还有那 看到了么
There and there, do you see?

56
00:04:56,834 --> 00:04:58,438
常春藤被拉开了
The ivy's pulled away.

57
00:04:59,373 --> 00:05:00,935
我肯定是吓晕了
I must have fainted.

58
00:05:00,972 --> 00:05:03,111
醒来时天已经亮了
The next thing I knew it was dawn.

59
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:13,927
你能肯定你不是在做梦 Edith?
You're quite, quite certain you didn't dream this, Edith?

60
00:05:13,964 --> 00:05:15,346
我肯定
Quite.

61
00:05:17,634 --> 00:05:20,641
Jack 我要你全心全意地相信我
Jack, I insist you believe me.

62
00:05:22,379 --> 00:05:23,458
好吧
Very well.

63
00:05:23,495 --> 00:05:25,760
我要你去把这些事告诉福尔摩斯
And that you inform Sherlock Holmes of the facts.

64
00:05:25,797 --> 00:05:27,035
噢 亲爱的
Oh, darling.

65
00:05:27,417 --> 00:05:30,556
不然我就要重新考虑我们的婚事
Or I shall reconsider our engagement.

66
00:05:30,593 --> 00:05:32,382
为什么
But why?

67
00:05:33,107 --> 00:05:37,930
我不能和一个不相信我的人 携手共度此生
I could not give my hand to a man who doubts my word.

68
00:06:36,206 --> 00:06:39,500
<i>华生 如方便请前来</i>
<i>Watson, come at once if convenient.</i>

69
00:06:41,579 --> 00:06:44,149
<i>不方便亦来</i>
<i>If inconvenient come all the same.</i>

70
00:06:49,114 --> 00:06:52,374
福尔摩斯 我收到了你的便条
Holmes, I got your note

71
00:06:52,488 --> 00:06:54,598
是不方便
and it is inconvenient,

72
00:06:54,713 --> 00:06:55,931
确实不方便
damned inconvenient.

73
00:06:55,968 --> 00:06:57,889
你的旧伤又在困扰你了
Your old wound is troubling you.

74
00:06:58,469 --> 00:06:59,384
没有的事
No.

75
00:06:59,421 --> 00:07:00,076
我看未必
I prefer to differ.

76
00:07:00,114 --> 00:07:02,616
你上楼时脚步不稳
Your step was uneven on the stairs.

77
00:07:03,025 --> 00:07:04,684
我做了一天的手术 福尔摩斯
I have a full surgery Holmes.

78
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:08,723
你得原谅  我有点走神
You must excuse a certain abstraction of mind, Watson.

79
00:07:08,832 --> 00:07:09,637
我知道
I see.

80
00:07:09,675 --> 00:07:11,481
这件事很复杂
It's a tangled scheme.

81
00:07:12,496 --> 00:07:15,389
我正努力找出头绪
I've been looking for the loose end which might unravel it.

82
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:19,231
以便解决它
One such might reside in the question,

83
00:07:19,267 --> 00:07:24,367
问题的关键在于到底Presbury教授的女儿 是清醒的还是在做梦
does Professor Presbury's daughter wake or dream.

84
00:07:26,326 --> 00:07:28,904
你把我叫来 就为这么个事儿?
I'm summoned here for no more than this?

85
00:07:30,047 --> 00:07:31,820
你肯定听说过Presbury?
You've heard of Presbury?

86
00:07:32,675 --> 00:07:34,300
当然 谁没听说过呢?
Of course, who hasn't?

87
00:07:34,429 --> 00:07:37,518
我们最著名的自然科学家
He's our most distinguished natural scientist.

88
00:07:37,628 --> 00:07:39,450
他是个鳏夫 有一个女儿
He's a widower with one daughter.

89
00:07:39,488 --> 00:07:43,338
他女儿坚持说 夜里有人在她窗边出现
She insists someone appeared at her window last night.

90
00:07:45,887 --> 00:07:49,935
Presbury小姐的卧室在三楼
Ms. Presbury's bedroom is on the second floor

91
00:07:49,972 --> 00:07:53,894
即使是最敏捷的飞贼也没法爬上去
and is completely inaccessible to even the most agile cat burglar.

92
00:07:53,931 --> 00:07:55,060
读一读这个
Read this.

93
00:07:55,449 --> 00:07:57,547
是一点钟的邮车送来的
It arrived by the 1:00 post.

94
00:08:02,254 --> 00:08:04,855
写信的人已经提前来了
The author already arrives ahead of his time,

95
00:08:04,963 --> 00:08:06,943
真是个非常性急的年轻人
a most precipitant young man.

96
00:08:07,049 --> 00:08:09,336
Bennett先生 这是我的朋友和同事华生
Mr. Bennett, my friend and colleague Dr. Watson.

97
00:08:09,448 --> 00:08:10,176
您好
How do you do?

98
00:08:10,214 --> 00:08:10,998
Bennett先生
Mr. Bennett.

99
00:08:11,034 --> 00:08:11,726
请坐
Please sit down.

100
00:08:11,763 --> 00:08:13,211
不 请原谅
No, forgive me.

101
00:08:13,873 --> 00:08:16,848
福尔摩斯先生 恐怕我的判断严重有误
Mr. Holmes, I fear I've made a grave error of judgment.

102
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:19,700
我本来是不该来找您的
I should not have been in touch with you at all.

103
00:08:19,737 --> 00:08:21,597
我是在浪费你的时间
I've wasted your time entirely.

104
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:24,575
没有什么合理的理由 能解释Presbury小姐的恐惧
It is not a rational reason for Ms. Presbury's fears.

105
00:08:24,612 --> 00:08:26,108
是的 是无法解释
No, no I can't say that.

106
00:08:26,144 --> 00:08:29,135
这事很微妙
Well it's, it's a delicate matter but I,

107
00:08:29,172 --> 00:08:31,237
我必须请求您不要再继续了
I must beg you to proceed no further.

108
00:08:31,274 --> 00:08:33,392
当然 我会补偿你的
I can of course recompense you.

109
00:08:37,775 --> 00:08:40,545
Bennett先生 你在信里有所隐瞒
Mr. Bennett, your letter was less than frank,

110
00:08:40,582 --> 00:08:41,906
是不是?
was it not?

111
00:08:41,943 --> 00:08:44,275
我说出了全部事实
I set out the facts.

112
00:08:44,312 --> 00:08:46,542
我怀疑不是全部
Not all I suspect.

113
00:08:46,578 --> 00:08:49,868
或许是出于对未婚妻Presbury小姐的忠诚?
Probably out of loyalty to your fiance, Ms. Presbury?

114
00:08:49,905 --> 00:08:50,831
您听说过她?
You're aware of her?

115
00:08:50,869 --> 00:08:54,645
当然 我还听说 你的雇主跟Alice Morphy小姐订了婚
As I am of your employer's engagement to Ms. Alice Morphy,

116
00:08:54,975 --> 00:08:57,750
她可是著名解剖学家的女儿啊
the daughter of the famous comparative anatomist.

117
00:08:57,787 --> 00:09:00,425
她与Presburys家是邻居 是么?
She resides next door to the Presburys, does she not?

118
00:09:00,462 --> 00:09:02,335
你怎么知道他们订婚了?
How do you know of the engagement?

119
00:09:02,372 --> 00:09:06,430
婚讯就登在泰晤士报上 分别是七月一日和九月五日
The Times, July the 1st, September the 5th respectively.

120
00:09:07,719 --> 00:09:11,269
福尔摩斯先生可以说是过目不忘
Mr. Holmes' memory is of a photographical order.

121
00:09:11,306 --> 00:09:12,431
确实是这样
Quite so.

122
00:09:13,223 --> 00:09:15,166
哦 天哪
Oh, dear.

123
00:09:16,342 --> 00:09:19,184
Bennett 我了解你的窘境
Mr. Bennett, I do appreciate your predicament.

124
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:21,567
作为一个科学家 一个理性主义者
As a scientist and a rationalist yourself

125
00:09:21,604 --> 00:09:24,311
你不愿意采纳
I dare say you're reluctant to accept the evidence

126
00:09:24,349 --> 00:09:26,183
Presbury小姐所坚持的证据
insisted upon by Ms. Presbury.

127
00:09:26,219 --> 00:09:28,684
况且 作为她父亲信任的助手
Further, as a father's trusted assistant

128
00:09:28,721 --> 00:09:31,420
向我求助也陷你于不忠
to have recourse to me must smack to you of disloyalty.

129
00:09:31,457 --> 00:09:32,587
一点不错
Exactly.

130
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:35,222
我是这个家庭的一份子
I'm part of the family except that Edith,

131
00:09:35,552 --> 00:09:38,091
除非Presbury小姐因为不安而...
Ms. Presbury, she was so upset that she,

132
00:09:38,128 --> 00:09:41,142
