你让我陷入两难 都不是
You give me a choice of evils, neither.

135
00:09:46,570 --> 00:09:48,118
那就多告诉我一些事实
Then furnish me with the facts

136
00:09:48,155 --> 00:09:50,130
看我能不能帮助你
and I will see how I can help you.

137
00:09:50,863 --> 00:09:53,710
你可以依赖我们两个的判断力
You may rely on the discretion of both of us.

138
00:09:55,917 --> 00:09:56,873
好吧
Well.

139
00:09:57,529 --> 00:10:01,426
比如说 你会不会把Presbury小姐
Would you for example describe Ms. Presbury,

140
00:10:01,463 --> 00:10:04,240
描述成一个敏感爱幻想的女孩?
as an impressionable, fanciful girl?

141
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:07,475
不 恰恰相反
No, quite the reverse.

142
00:10:07,511 --> 00:10:09,359
那么Alice Morphy小姐呢
Ms. Alice Morphy?

143
00:10:09,397 --> 00:10:11,633
或许Presbury教授和她订婚
Perhaps Professor Presbury's engagement to her

144
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:13,721
让你感到意外
came to you as something of a surprise.

145
00:10:14,088 --> 00:10:17,473
毕竟他的年龄是她的三倍
He is after all three times her age.

146
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:19,441
选这件天鹅绒的?
And this velour?

147
00:10:20,301 --> 00:10:21,869
我更中意
I prefer that one,

148
00:10:21,905 --> 00:10:23,749
带白色羽毛的那一件
with the osprey feathers.

149
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:28,344
你能去问问他么
Could you ask him, do you think?

150
00:10:29,263 --> 00:10:32,458
我父亲对他的兰花最自豪了
Father's extremely proud of his orchids.

151
00:10:32,496 --> 00:10:34,418
我讨厌它们
I hate them.

152
00:10:35,481 --> 00:10:37,195
它们是那么的
They're so,

153
00:10:37,231 --> 00:10:41,278
怎么说呢 那么的不纯洁
oh I don't know, so impure somehow.

154
00:10:42,434 --> 00:10:44,395
你去跟他说别再送兰花了 好么
Do please ask him not to send them anymore.

155
00:10:44,432 --> 00:10:46,813
我就你这么一个好朋友了 求求你
There's a sweet friend, Edith, please?

156
00:10:46,919 --> 00:10:48,916
-你自己不能去说么 -不
-Can you not ask him? -I couldn't.

157
00:10:50,003 --> 00:10:52,408
我不敢 我很懦弱的
I dare not. I'm such a coward.

158
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:54,777
-恩 -求求你了
-Well. -Oh, please?

159
00:10:54,814 --> 00:10:57,308
你比我要有个性的多
You've got so much more character than me.

160
00:10:57,421 --> 00:10:58,677
跟他一样有很强的个性
You're as strong as he.

161
00:10:58,714 --> 00:11:00,479
可是Alice
But Alice,

162
00:11:00,516 --> 00:11:03,439
如果你连这个都不敢对我父亲说
if you dare not ask this of my father

163
00:11:03,476 --> 00:11:06,041
那结婚以后 你怎么去处理那些
how will you ever manage those deeper conflicts

164
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:09,326
即使是最幸福的婚姻中也会存在的冲突呢
that occur even in the happiest of marriages?

165
00:11:09,364 --> 00:11:10,762
我不知道
Oh, I don't know.

166
00:11:12,945 --> 00:11:14,659
我很害怕
I'm so frightened.

167
00:11:14,696 --> 00:11:16,285
害怕和我父亲结婚?
Of marrying my father?

168
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:18,018
我想是的
I wish,

169
00:11:19,076 --> 00:11:21,026
请别再问了
no, please don't ask.

170
00:11:21,064 --> 00:11:23,051
我们别再谈这个了
Let's not speak of it.

171
00:11:27,164 --> 00:11:29,048
你觉得这个怎么样?
What do you think of this one?

172
00:11:29,590 --> 00:11:33,581
不论是Presbury小姐还是我 都认为她父亲对Morphy小姐的迷恋
Neither Ms. Presbury nor I consider her father's infatuation with Ms. Morphy to be

173
00:11:34,323 --> 00:11:36,318
总的说来不是很合适
... entirely appropriate.

174
00:11:36,649 --> 00:11:38,107
有点极端
Rather excessive.

175
00:11:38,214 --> 00:11:40,795
她的父母 对这门亲事也没有反对吗?
And her parents have no objections to the marriage?

176
00:11:41,663 --> 00:11:44,198
教授是个受人尊敬的鳏夫
The professor is a respectable widower.

177
00:11:44,236 --> 00:11:45,584
而且还很富有
And a wealthy man.

178
00:11:51,803 --> 00:11:53,389
我什么时候能去拜访?
When may I call?

179
00:11:53,427 --> 00:11:54,952
拜访?
Call?

180
00:11:54,988 --> 00:11:57,361
去查看Presbury小姐的窗口
To view Ms. Presbury's window,

181
00:11:57,666 --> 00:11:59,684
亲自去判断
to determine for myself its accessibility

182
00:11:59,721 --> 00:12:00,884
是否存在有人闯入的可能
and otherwise to an intruder.

183
00:12:00,921 --> 00:12:02,661
明天早上11点可以么?
Shall we say 11:00 tomorrow morning?

184
00:12:02,698 --> 00:12:04,455
教授那时会在学校里
Professor Presbury will be at his college.

185
00:12:04,492 --> 00:12:05,135
那就没有问题了
That's of no matter.

186
00:12:05,172 --> 00:12:07,612
我的请求完全合理
At present my inquiries are purely logistical.

187
00:12:07,649 --> 00:12:10,947
我对教授从没有什么隐瞒的
I have never had any secrets from the professor.

188
00:12:10,985 --> 00:12:12,396
Bennett先生
Mr. Bennett,

189
00:12:13,056 --> 00:12:15,024
让我提醒你
let me refer you to your first question,

190
00:12:15,061 --> 00:12:16,809
你事实上已经回答了我的第一个问题
which you have in fact answered.

191
00:12:17,229 --> 00:12:20,044
比起你的雇主
You're more inclined to Ms. Presbury's party

192
00:12:20,081 --> 00:12:21,946
你更倾向于Presbury小姐一方
than you are to your employer's.

193
00:12:24,649 --> 00:12:26,372
是的 我想是这样
Yes, yes, I dare say.

194
00:12:26,409 --> 00:12:27,657
谢谢
Thank you.

195
00:12:27,693 --> 00:12:28,965
再见
Good day.

196
00:12:31,260 --> 00:12:32,284
再见
Good day.

197
00:12:42,163 --> 00:12:46,027
福尔摩斯 你这是在刺探 一个受人尊敬的家庭的家务事
Holmes, you're prying into the affairs of a perfectly respectable family.

198
00:12:46,064 --> 00:12:48,543
为什么Bennett这么不情愿说出实情?
Why is Bennett so reluctant to tell the truth?

199
00:12:48,580 --> 00:12:49,364
忠诚
Loyalty.

200
00:12:49,401 --> 00:12:50,859
这是显而易见的
It is as plain as a pack staff.

201
00:12:50,896 --> 00:12:52,160
但愿如此
Let us hope so.

202
00:12:52,197 --> 00:12:54,200
但他却是被迫写信给我的
Yet he wrote to me under duress.

203
00:12:54,631 --> 00:12:56,620
你注意到他的笔迹了么
You notice his handwriting,

204
00:12:56,656 --> 00:12:59,864
字母T下笔很重
the crossing of the T's with such deep indentation?

205
00:12:59,974 --> 00:13:02,258
还有他刚来的时候 努力要取消这件事
And then upon his arrival his endeavors to call the whole thing off, 

206
00:13:02,259 --> 00:13:04,040
不 这件事可不是看上去的这么简单
no, there's more to this than meets the eye.

207
00:13:04,077 --> 00:13:04,841
我不同意
I do not agree.

208
00:13:04,878 --> 00:13:07,960
杀鸡焉用宰牛刀
This case is unworthy of you.

209
00:13:10,545 --> 00:13:12,514
我得回诊所去了
I must return to my surgery.

210
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:15,705
或许明天再见喽
Maybe I'll see you tomorrow.

211
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:56,154
父亲
Father?

212
00:13:56,383 --> 00:13:57,660
亲爱的
My dear.

213
00:13:58,469 --> 00:14:00,199
我想你昨晚睡得好点了吧?
I trust you slept better?

214
00:14:00,313 --> 00:14:01,169
哦 是的
Oh, yes.

215
00:14:01,205 --> 00:14:03,616
昨晚我搬到客房去睡了
Last night I moved to the guest bedroom.

216
00:14:03,653 --> 00:14:05,525
没这个必要
Oh, no need surely.

217
00:14:05,562 --> 00:14:08,178
那只是场噩梦
It was but an ugly dream.

218
00:14:08,770 --> 00:14:12,056
父亲 Alice要我...
Father, Alice has asked me,

219
00:14:12,806 --> 00:14:13,970
什么?
Yes?

220
00:14:14,913 --> 00:14:18,064
实际上她根本不喜欢兰花
The truth is she does not care for orchids.

221
00:14:19,938 --> 00:14:21,552
她不喜欢?
She doesn't?

222
00:14:23,366 --> 00:14:25,537
那她为什么不说呢
Well, why did she not say so?

223
00:14:25,574 --> 00:14:27,481
她不敢说
Well, she was afraid to.

224
00:14:27,518 --> 00:14:31,050
您不知道您是多么令人畏惧
You forget how formidable you are father.

225
00:14:32,516 --> 00:14:34,222
傻女孩
The silly girl.

226
00:14:34,672 --> 00:14:37,032
那她会收到玫瑰的
Well, then she shall have roses.

227
00:14:37,069 --> 00:14:40,576
两打红玫瑰
Yes, two dozen red roses.

228
00:14:47,540 --> 00:14:50,420
Roy昨晚很安静
Roy was quiet enough last night.

229
00:14:50,530 --> 00:14:51,903
别激怒它 先生
Not to rouse him, sir.

230
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:55,546
它本来很温顺的
Docility itself, (unintelligible).

231
00:14:56,957 --> 00:14:58,157
好吧
All right,

232
00:14:58,194 --> 00:15:01,385
它会适应这些锁链的
He's grown accustomed to his shackles.

233
00:15:01,422 --> 00:15:03,511
可怜的家伙
The poor beast.

234
00:15:12,822 --> 00:15:14,036
我们可以上去么
Shall we go up?

235
00:15:14,073 --> 00:15:16,120
如果Presbury小姐不反对的话
If Ms. Presbury has no objection.

236
00:15:16,231 --> 00:15:18,139
我明白必须这么做
I understand the necessity.

237
00:15:18,175 --> 00:15:20,531
我们来带路吧 亲爱的
Let us lead the way my dear.

238
00:15:24,248 --> 00:15:26,829
我很高兴你今天恢复正常了 华生
I'm glad you're more yourself today, Watson.

239
00:15:27,046 --> 00:15:29,511
你昨天简直像是头熊
You were a veritable bear yesterday.

240
00:15:29,619 --> 00:15:32,215
或许有点脾气不好
A touch liverish perhaps.

241
00:15:36,992 --> 00:15:38,486
就是这出现了人影?
This is where the figure appeared?

242
00:15:38,592 --> 00:15:39,563
是的
Yes.

243
00:15:39,671 --> 00:15:41,004
没有什么梯子
There's no ladder on the premises

244
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:42,622
能伸到这个高度吧
that could reach this height?

245
00:15:42,730 --> 00:15:43,641
没有
No.

246
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:45,821
窗子是半开着的?
Was the window ajar?

247
00:15:45,930 --> 00:15:48,468
是的 我把门锁了
Yes, I keep the door locked.

248
00:15:50,277 --> 00:15:52,479
他的手碰到窗玻璃了么?
Did the hand touch the windowpane?

249
00:15:52,642 --> 00:15:53,921
我不知道
I don't know.

250
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:55,527
我晕过去了
I fainted.

251
00:15:55,633 --> 00:15:57,954
你当然会的 当然
Of course you did, of course you did.

252
00:16:01,962 --> 00:16:04,451
这是令人生畏的高度
Well, that's a formidable elevation,

253
00:16:06,344 --> 00:16:11,357
尽管常春藤很牢固
yet the ivy's strong, Hedera Helixis,

254
00:16:11,526 --> 00:16:13,617
但在那还是给扯断了
torn away just here.

255
00:16:17,682 --> 00:16:21,670
Presbury小姐 你父亲提前回来了
Ms. Presbury, your father has returned prematurely.

256
00:16:21,706 --> 00:16:22,438
哦 不
Oh, no.

257
00:16:22,476 --> 00:16:24,144
不能让他知道你在这里 福尔摩斯先生
He mustn't know you're here Mr. Holmes.

258
00:16:24,181 --> 00:16:26,030
这没法避免
That can scarcely be avoided.

259
00:16:26,067 --> 00:16:27,929
不管怎么说 我们先下去吧
However, let us go down.

260
00:16:28,045 --> 00:16:29,325
从后楼梯?
The backstairs?

261
00:16:29,437 --> 00:16:30,888
当然不是
Certainly not.

262
00:16:36,357 --> 00:16:40,460
Bennett 你是怎么准备我的讲座的?
Bennett, what did you do with my lecture?

263
00:16:42,269 --> 00:16:44,781
你到底是谁 先生?
Who the devil are you, sir?

264
00:16:45,224 --> 00:16:47,690
父亲 对不起
Father, I'm sorry.

265
00:16:47,728 --> 00:16:49,470
这是歇洛克・福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Sherlock Holmes.

266
00:16:49,507 --> 00:16:51,289
谁?
Who?

267
00:16:51,326 --> 00:16:52,343
著名侦探
The detective.

268
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:54,127
Presbury教授
Professor Presbury,

269
00:16:55,228 --> 00:16:56,754
我的名片
my card.

270
00:17:01,292 --> 00:17:05,310
221 B
221 B,

271
00:17:05,603 --> 00:17:08,813
这么个地址很难激起别人的信任
hardly an address to inspire confidence.

272
00:17:09,707 --> 00:17:12,027
我从没想过要激起别人的信任
I have never sought to inspire confidence in others.

273
00:17:12,065 --> 00:17:13,220
我对自己倒是信心十足
I have quite enough of my own.

274
00:17:13,256 --> 00:17:14,941
我来介绍我的同事 华生医生
May I introduce my colleague Dr. Watson?

275
00:17:14,979 --> 00:17:17,031
不必了 你们俩都可以马上离开
Certainly not, you may leave at once the pair of you.

276
00:17:17,068 --> 00:17:19,546
父亲 他们是我们请来的客人
Father, they are here at our request.

277
00:17:19,653 --> 00:17:21,597
我可没有请他们 Edith
But not mine, Edith.

278
00:17:21,706 --> 00:17:23,258
至于你 Bennett
And you Bennett,

279
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:26,547
在你寻求用这种解决方式前应该和我商量
you should have consulted me before resorting to such methods,

280
00:17:26,585 --> 00:17:30,793
一个平庸的侦探和他的同伙
a common detective and his accomplice, really.

281
00:17:30,921 --> 00:17:32,193
现在 先生们
Now, sir,

282
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:34,661
我来护送你们从这里出去
allow me to escort you from the premises.

283
00:17:36,172 --> 00:17:38,925
我的助手没有权力雇佣你处理这件事
My assistant had no authority to engage you in this matter.

284
00:17:38,962 --> 00:17:40,618
别再调查它了
Kindly inquire into it no further.

285
00:17:40,655 --> 00:17:42,874
不然的话我会
Should you persist I shall have no hesitation

286
00:17:42,989 --> 00:17:44,500
毫不犹豫的叫警察的
in calling the police.

287
00:17:44,537 --> 00:17:46,461
我和苏格兰场的Lestrade可很熟 所以你最好小心点
Lestrade of Yard is well known to me so beware.

288
00:17:46,498 --> 00:17:48,827
去找Lestrade嘛 我可是会犹疑的 教授
I would hesitate in calling Lestrade, professor,

289
00:17:48,936 --> 00:17:51,010
如果你希望解开这个谜的话
if you wish to have the mystery solved.

290
00:17:51,127 --> 00:17:54,276
压根就没有什么谜 先生 没有
There is no mystery, sir, none.

291
00:17:54,675 --> 00:17:55,793
现在你们可以走了
Now be gone with you

292
00:17:55,830 --> 00:17:58,160
否则我就要放狗了
or would you have me release my dog?

293
00:17:58,291 --> 00:17:59,905
它可分不清
Believe me he'll not distinguish

294
00:17:59,941 --> 00:18:03,832
谁是雇来的私家侦探 谁是入侵者
between a hired snoop and an intruder.

295
00:18:05,385 --> 00:18:07,690
你们还不走吗 先生们?
Will you be gone, sir, will you?

296
00:18:07,727 --> 00:18:09,551
我们会走的 你也别太过分了
We shall, sir, we shall but you are over the mark.

297
00:18:09,663 --> 00:18:11,430
说话要小心点
Kindly watch your words.

298
00:18:11,541 --> 00:18:12,976
这个品种的狗
As a breed,

299
00:18:13,013 --> 00:18:14,622
虽然外表很凶猛
despite their ferocious appearance

300
00:18:14,659 --> 00:18:16,598
实际上举止却并不凶猛
these dogs are seldom vicious.

301
00:18:17,423 --> 00:18:20,976
我很奇怪Roy为什么要整天拴着
I'm surprised that Roy needs chaining at all

302
00:18:21,013 --> 00:18:24,201
除非是为了你的安全吧
unless it is for your safety as much as ours.

303
00:19:03,428 --> 00:19:06,582
华生 狗能反映一个家庭的生活
The dog reflects family life Watson.

304
00:19:06,697 --> 00:19:08,916
真的么
Does it indeed.

305
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,880
谁听说过在阴郁的家庭里有只欢闹的狗
Whoever heard of a frisky dog in a gloomy home

306
00:19:12,991 --> 00:19:15,580
或是在欢乐的家里有只悲伤的狗?
or a sad dog in a happy one?

307
00:19:16,469 --> 00:19:19,465
易怒的人养着易怒的狗
Snarling people have snarling dogs.

308
00:19:19,982 --> 00:19:23,586
你像我一样注意到了 Presbury家的爱尔兰猎狗
You observed the Presbury's Irish wolfhound as well as I.

309
00:19:23,623 --> 00:19:25,684
它对它的主人咆哮着
He growled quite as much at his master as it did at us,

310
00:19:25,789 --> 00:19:27,447
就像对待我们两个陌生人一样
two complete strangers.

311
00:19:27,563 --> 00:19:30,761
这动物毫不掩饰它对教授的敌意
That animal did not reserve its animosity solely for the professor.

312
00:19:30,798 --> 00:19:34,096
等一会Bennett来了 我们会从他那确认这一点的
We'll seek verification from young Bennett when he arrives.

313
00:19:34,134 --> 00:19:36,927
我们在"山羊罗盘"酒馆会面后
I sent word by way of Jack Macphail

314
00:19:36,964 --> 00:19:39,421
我顺道给Jack Macphail捎了信
after our meeting at the Goat and Compasses.

315
00:19:40,131 --> 00:19:41,743
你的另一个密探么 福尔摩斯?
Another of your agents Holmes?

316
00:19:41,857 --> 00:19:43,692
是Presbury家的马车夫
The Presburys' coachman.

317
00:19:43,728 --> 00:19:45,818
他负责看管Roy
He has charge of Roy.

318
00:19:46,726 --> 00:19:50,179
我昨晚跟他一起去找了个小小的乐子
I joined him last night for what he calls a wee Goldie.

319
00:19:50,216 --> 00:19:51,893
Bennett来了 还是那么风风火火
Here's Bennett, precipitous as ever.

320
00:19:51,930 --> 00:19:53,019
请进
Come in.

321
00:19:54,523 --> 00:19:55,717
早上好
Good morning.

322
00:19:57,969 --> 00:20:00,195
福尔摩斯先生 华生医生
Mr. Holmes, Dr. Watson,

323
00:20:00,929 --> 00:20:04,027
我必须为昨天的会面道歉
I must apologize for your unfortunate encounter yesterday.

324
00:20:04,332 --> 00:20:06,522
-但同时... -没必要
-But also... -There's no need.

325
00:20:06,559 --> 00:20:08,640
事实上 恰好给这件怪事
In fact, it has provided the very first clue

326
00:20:08,677 --> 00:20:09,707
提供了第一个线索
to this odd affair.

327
00:20:09,744 --> 00:20:11,145
请坐
Do sit down.

328
00:20:11,181 --> 00:20:12,503
谢谢
Thank you.

329
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:15,198
福尔摩斯先生 我不能装作
Mr. Holmes, I cannot pretend that I am happy

330
00:20:15,311 --> 00:20:16,901
接到你的邀请时很高兴
to have answered your summons.

331
00:20:16,938 --> 00:20:20,320
当然 我仍然欣赏你
Of course and I continue to appreciate

332
00:20:20,357 --> 00:20:21,749
那分裂的忠诚
the division of your loyalties.

333
00:20:21,786 --> 00:20:24,987
所以你有些事情没有坦诚以告也不足为奇
It's no small wonder that you've withheld so much.

334
00:20:30,171 --> 00:20:32,359
Roy第一次袭击它的主人
Roy first attacked his master on the evening

335
00:20:32,396 --> 00:20:34,411
是在九月二日的晚上 是么?
of September the 2nd, did he not?

336
00:20:34,448 --> 00:20:35,715
你是怎么知道的?
How can you know that?

337
00:20:35,753 --> 00:20:37,851
就在教授从书房去到门厅的时候
As the professor came from his study into the hall

338
00:20:37,888 --> 00:20:39,602
在这种情况下
he restrained the dog.

339
00:20:39,639 --> 00:20:42,375
他拴住狗 把它关在储藏室里
On this occasion he was merely shut up in the scullery.

340
00:20:42,412 --> 00:20:44,277
第二天早晨又一切正常了
The next morning he was as right as rain

341
00:20:44,314 --> 00:20:46,083
这都是Macphail告诉我的
or so Macphail informs me.

342
00:20:46,711 --> 00:20:47,895
Macphail?
Macphail?

343
00:20:47,932 --> 00:20:48,974
还有谁能比家里的马车夫
Who better than the family coachman

344
00:20:49,011 --> 00:20:52,601
更能告诉我实情呢?
to advise me how matters might truly stand?

345
00:20:54,402 --> 00:20:56,871
请原谅 福尔摩斯先生 我应该亲自告诉你这些 但是...
Forgive me Mr. Holmes, I should have told you myself but...

346
00:20:56,907 --> 00:20:58,163
但是你没有
But you didn't.

347
00:20:58,615 --> 00:21:01,454
第二次袭击是在13天后
The second attack occurred 13 days later.

348
00:21:01,565 --> 00:21:03,402
同样 教授是在门厅里
Again, the professor was in the hall.

349
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:06,440
幸运的是 这一次他关上了书房的门
Fortunately this time he was able to put the study door between himself

350
00:21:06,478 --> 00:21:08,486
挡住了狗 是不是这样?
and the altered animal, was he not?

351
00:21:08,522 --> 00:21:11,045
就是从那会起 Edith希望把Roy锁起来
Edith wanted Roy chained from that moment.

352
00:21:11,082 --> 00:21:13,005
但她父亲不同意
But her father overruled her.

353
00:21:13,042 --> 00:21:16,257
他坚持说它还是条可爱温柔的狗
He insisted that he was still a dear affectionate dog,

354
00:21:16,294 --> 00:21:18,041
本性上不会伤人
that he wasn't congenitally vicious.

355
00:21:18,078 --> 00:21:20,918
那在第三次袭击后呢?
But not after the third attack?

356
00:21:20,955 --> 00:21:23,761
不 他再没有这么说 而是把狗栓了起来
No, he did agree then that he had to be restrained.

357
00:21:23,798 --> 00:21:27,150
然后Roy就被这么被锁在马房里了?
And Roy was banished to the chain in the stable yard.

358
00:21:27,187 --> 00:21:28,414
是的
Yes.

359
00:21:28,451 --> 00:21:30,723
Macphail认为Roy行为的变化
Macphail believes that the change in Roy's behavior

360
00:21:30,760 --> 00:21:32,832
大约是两个月前出现的
stems from about two months ago?

361
00:21:33,474 --> 00:21:34,459
我想或许是的
I think it may have.

362
00:21:34,568 --> 00:21:36,238
我没有特别注意
I, I didn't keep a straight note of it.

363
00:21:36,275 --> 00:21:38,461
去问问你的未婚妻 还有Macphail
Consult your fiance Bennett and Macphail.

364
00:21:38,498 --> 00:21:40,095
关于这件事 有必要做一个
A precise log of these events

365
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,592
确切的记录
may yet prove pertinent.

366
00:21:41,697 --> 00:21:43,655
我注意到教授今天下午
I observed that the professor lectures

367
00:21:43,691 --> 00:21:46,316
两点钟在大学里有个讲座
at the university at 2:00 this afternoon.

368
00:21:46,353 --> 00:21:47,925
到时我会到家里去
I shall call then.

369
00:21:47,962 --> 00:21:51,402
不 我不同意
No, I couldn't possibly agree, no.

370
00:21:51,439 --> 00:21:55,206
Bennett  Presbury小姐不是在做梦
Bennett, Ms. Presbury did not dream.

371
00:21:55,889 --> 00:21:58,426
是有什么人或什么东西探访了她
Someone or something looked in upon her.

372
00:21:58,928 --> 00:22:02,648
