It is my conviction that your fiance is in grave danger.

373
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:04,732
来自谁?
From who?

374
00:22:04,770 --> 00:22:10,137
不 先生 应该说是来自什么东西
No, sir, from whom or from what.

375
00:22:16,092 --> 00:22:19,384
作为秘书 你负责处理教授的通信
As secretary you handle the professor's correspondence.

376
00:22:19,421 --> 00:22:22,321
是的 我的职责是是拆阅每一封信
Oh yes, it's my responsibility to open every letter.

377
00:22:23,115 --> 00:22:24,996
Presbury小姐一直习惯于
Has it always been Ms. Presbury's habit

378
00:22:25,034 --> 00:22:27,149
每天晚上锁上卧室的门么
to lock her bedroom door at night?

379
00:22:29,359 --> 00:22:33,212
呃 不
Um, no, well it,

380
00:22:33,249 --> 00:22:34,968
她告诉我...
well she told me that...

381
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,574
什么?
Yes?

382
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:38,754
那是在Roy举止怪异之后
It was after Roy began to behave so strangely.

383
00:22:38,871 --> 00:22:41,502
她也开始害怕狗了么
That she too became afraid of the dog?

384
00:22:41,618 --> 00:22:43,241
福尔摩斯先生 你不能碰他的书桌
Mr. Holmes, you mustn't touch his desk.

385
00:22:43,356 --> 00:22:44,392
Bennett!
Bennett!

386
00:22:45,456 --> 00:22:46,994
谢谢
Thank you.

387
00:23:00,814 --> 00:23:02,472
告诉我教授和这个叫
Inform me of the correspondence

388
00:23:02,588 --> 00:23:08,908
Dorak的通信情况
the professor had with someone called Dorak

389
00:23:09,022 --> 00:23:14,334
住在Com Read
inhabiting Com Read.

390
00:23:14,447 --> 00:23:17,186
不
No, no, no,

391
00:23:17,299 --> 00:23:21,887
商业街 当然(头字母为CC)
Commercial Road of course CC.

392
00:23:21,994 --> 00:23:23,903
似乎教授本人
It would appear that the professor answers

393
00:23:24,011 --> 00:23:26,631
亲自回复此人的信件
such correspondence himself.

394
00:23:27,036 --> 00:23:28,660
嗯 又是...
Well, again...

395
00:23:28,775 --> 00:23:31,869
又是吞吞吐吐的了
Again, you've been reluctant to speak.

396
00:23:31,975 --> 00:23:33,363
是的
Yes.

397
00:23:34,270 --> 00:23:37,358
大约8周前 他告诉我
Some eight weeks ago he told me that

398
00:23:37,395 --> 00:23:38,993
有一些邮件从东区寄来
certain missives might arrive from East Central

399
00:23:39,104 --> 00:23:41,741
邮票上划着十字
marked by a cross under the stamp.

400
00:23:41,778 --> 00:23:42,823
一个密码?
A code?

401
00:23:44,919 --> 00:23:47,379
这些信是定期寄来的么?
And did they regularly?

402
00:23:47,416 --> 00:23:48,942
不是定期的
Irregularly.

403
00:23:48,979 --> 00:23:51,304
我不得拆阅 也不能跟别人说起
I was to leave them unopened and speak of them to no one.

404
00:23:51,416 --> 00:23:52,695
你说邮件
You said missive.

405
00:23:52,805 --> 00:23:54,085
不光是信么
They were not letters.

406
00:23:54,197 --> 00:23:56,397
有些是 还有些是小包裹
Well, some were, others were small packets.

407
00:23:56,806 --> 00:23:59,334
你注意到 Presbury教授如何回复么?
And did you observe Professor Presbury's replies?

408
00:23:59,449 --> 00:24:00,091
不知道
No.

409
00:24:00,128 --> 00:24:01,452
这些都不由我经手
They didn't pass through my hands.

410
00:24:01,489 --> 00:24:04,880
但有证据表明他确实回信了
Yet the evidence would suggest that he did respond.

411
00:24:04,917 --> 00:24:08,562
印度人认为 狗是猴子的天敌
To the Hindu the dog is a traditional enemy of the monkey.

412
00:24:08,599 --> 00:24:10,612
这说明什么 华生?
What was that Watson?

413
00:24:11,414 --> 00:24:12,539
什么?
What?

414
00:24:12,575 --> 00:24:13,415
没什么
Nothing.

415
00:24:13,452 --> 00:24:14,983
Jack?
Jack?

416
00:24:16,268 --> 00:24:18,855
哦 我不知道...
Oh, I, I wasn't aware.

417
00:24:19,481 --> 00:24:22,081
我没来得及告诉你 你已经出去了
No, I couldn't tell you, you'd already gone out.

418
00:24:22,118 --> 00:24:23,182
我知道了
I see.

419
00:24:24,175 --> 00:24:26,988
我邀请Alice来和我们喝茶
I've invited Alice to take tea with us.

420
